{
  "texts": [
    "The first is to what extent GPT-4 and humans differ in terms of semantic similarity to the vignettes they were trying to reappraise, and is similarity to the vignette associated with reappraisal quality?",
    "This investigation was driven from lay criticism of GPT-4, which is that despite being eloquent and detailed, its responses may be less tuned in to the specific scenarios produced by the vignettes.",
    "Our analysis of data from our studies suggested that GPT-4 and humans did not differ significantly in their degree of semantic similarity to the vignettes, but that reappraisals that were closer to the vignette were generally of higher quality (see detailed description below).",
    "The second question we were interested in answering is whether one of the reasons GPT-4 reappraisals seemed better is because the words produced by GPT-4 were more complex or may be interpreted as produced by someone with higher intelligence.",
    "We therefore compared the language complexity between humans and GPT-4 in our studies."
  ]
}